(21,	'Turkey',	0,	3,	'â€¢ Turkey is produced on a very small scale in most parts of Uganda. Currently there is no data available on quantities and locations of turkey production\r\nâ€¢ Diseases affecting Turkeys are similar to those affecting other poultry, including Newcastle, fowl cholera, coccidiosis, and pullorum disease.\r\n\r\n',	NULL,	7,	8000,	60000,	NULL,	'2011-03-28 21:29:01',	1,	NULL,	'2012-03-01 16:16:36'),
(22,	'Beef',	0,	5,	'â€¢ Beef production in Uganda uses predominantly indigenous breeds (approximately 95%).\r\nâ€¢ The Ugandan â€œcattle corridorâ€ stretches from Ntungamo in the West across the country to Kotido in the Northeast, taking in the districts of Ntungamo, Mbarara, Rakai, Kabarole, Mubende, Mpigi, Kiboga, Luwero, Apac, Lira, Soroti, Kumi, Mbale, Moroto, and Kotido.\r\n',	NULL,	5,	5000,	10000,	NULL,	'2011-03-28 21:29:01',	1,	NULL,	'2012-03-01 15:58:00'),
(23,	'Cavendish (Bogoya)',	0,	5,	'Also known as musa acuminata, musa nana, and musa sinensis.\r\nâ€¢ Cavendish is susceptible to diseases including Panama disease, tropical race 4, and black sigatoka.\r\nâ€¢ Cavendish is the most widely consumed and widely exported banana cultivar in the world, but production levels in Uganda are low by comparison with the apple banana. Cavendish production is mainly concentrated in Western and Eastern Uganda, the traditional banana-growing heartlands of the country.\r\n',	NULL,	11,	4000,	7000,	NULL,	'2011-03-28 21:29:01',	1,	NULL,	'2012-03-01 15:54:02'),
(24,	'Goat Meat',	0,	5,	'â€¢ The population of goats in Uganda is estimated at approximately\r\n4 million.\r\nâ€¢ Breeds of goat in Uganda include the small East African goat, the Mubende goat, and the Kigezi goat.\r\nâ€¢ Goats are kept in all districts of Uganda.\r\n',	NULL,	5,	4000,	9000,	NULL,	'2011-03-28 21:29:01',	1,	NULL,	'2012-03-01 16:05:25'),
(25,	'Nile Perch',	0,	5,	'â€¢ There are two species of Nile Perch in Uganda: Lates macrophthalmus and Lates niloticus.\r\nâ€¢ The species are native to Lake Albert, and the Albert Nile. They are also now found in Lake Victoria, and Lake Kyoga.\r\n',	NULL,	2,	4400,	20000,	NULL,	'2011-03-28 21:29:01',	1,	NULL,	'2012-03-01 16:04:43'),
(26,	'Tilapia',	0,	1,	'â€¢ Also known as Tilapiines and Ngege.\r\nâ€¢ The most commercially important and widely available fish in\r\nUganda.\r\nâ€¢ Various species sourced from Lakes Victoria, Kyoga, Albert, Edward, George, and other smaller bodies of water in Uganda.\r\n',	NULL,	2,	3500,	11000,	NULL,	'2011-03-28 21:29:01',	1,	NULL,	'2012-03-01 16:04:58'),
